The paper deals with the intersection of submonoids of a free monoid, which is a topic in formal language theory and automata theory. The use of automata-theoretic approach and the mention of semi-flower automata suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) sub-category. The mention of the Hanna Neumann property, which is a concept from group theory, suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GT (Group Theory) sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial and algebraic techniques, which are relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of a rank formula suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
